</span></li></ul></div></div></div><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" id="risks" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-126_"><a data-link="inherit" href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/blogs/hair-blog/everything-you-need-to-know-about-carrot-oil-for-hair#Index" target="_self"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-128_">Risks of Carrot Oil for Hair</span></a></h3><p class="sc-dYtuZ JoqQF pf-129_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-131_">Although there aren’t any specific studies concerning the risks of carrot oil, you should always practice caution when starting a new hair treatment and be mindful of the potential risks below.</span></p><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-132_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bXdNzS hYBROi pf-133_"><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-jNHqnW cbtrr pf-134_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-eSxRXt bYSBNX pf-135_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-137_"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Allergic Reactions<br></span>As with any supplement or topical treatment, the application of carrot oil for hair carries the risk of allergic reaction. Be sure to do a patch test before applying to your hair, and dilute carrot oil with a carrier oil (e.g., coconut oil) before applying to your skin.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-eSxRXt bYSBNX pf-138_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-140_"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Dying Hair and Scalp<br></span>While those with darker hair may be exempt from this, there is a risk that overuse of carrot oil could tint lighter hair and scalps orange. Use carrot oil sparingly (As with any treatment).&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-eSxRXt bYSBNX pf-141_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-143_"><span style="font-weight: 700;">General Warning<br></span>Anyone managing chronic medical scalp conditions should tread lightly when using any type of natural herbal oils or products, as we are unsure of the long-term impact on bacteria, fungi, and yeast.</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-144_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bXdNzS hYBROi pf-145_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" id="howtoapply" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-146_"><a data-link="inherit" href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/blogs/hair-blog/everything-you-need-to-know-about-carrot-oil-for-hair#Index" target="_self"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-148_">How To Apply Carrot Oil For Hair</span></a></h2><p class="sc-dYtuZ JoqQF pf-149_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-151_">There are many products on the market containing carrot extracts and oils (we list our faves below), if you’d prefer to use a <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/blogs/hair-blog/diy-aloe-vera-hair-treatment" target="_blank">DIY treatment</a> you can create your own <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/blogs/hair-blog/diy-vegan-hair-mask" target="_blank">hair mask at home</a>. For a simple oil application, dilute 3-4 drops of carrot essential oil with 2-4 tablespoons of a carrier oil such as coconut oil. Use oil sparingly depending on your hair type. Work the oil treatment through your hair while massaging it into your scalp. Comb through your hair, cover with a plastic cap and leave for an hour before washing out with shampoo. <br><br>To create a rinse, mix 3-4 drops of essential carrot oil with 2 cups of water and 1 teaspoon of apple cider vinegar. Apply to your hair after shampooing, leave for 5 minutes before rinsing again. 

